Some small 10” rounds and 7 lucky horseshoes will be available at the @eversonmuseum gift shop starting this Sunday. Also, my show opens tomorrow…this is all so wild I don’t even know what to do with myself. 
#fiberart #loominarium #eversonmuseum

Some finishing touches before tomorrow 😍 Reverie will be on view at @eversonmuseum March 18th until April 30th and I really hope some of you will be able to check it out. Months of work has gone into this show and I am so appreciative to the Everson and the CNY artist initiative for this incredible opportunity. I also want to thank all the spinners and other artists who contributed their art to make my art. We did it babes. #loominariumfiberart #fiberart #eversonmuseum

Who got to check out Reverie over the weekend? It is honestly so cool seeing my art on display at the @eversonmuseum. I will be there Wednesday at noon for a little chat about my weaving practice and stroll around the current exhibition- I hope to see you there! 
#AtTheE #fiberart #cnyartistinitiative

I still can’t get enough of this view. If you’re looking for something fun to do this weekend consider checking out Reverie at the @eversonmuseum ✨
#fiberart #syracuse #atthee

Sending soft love to everyone who needs it today. As we all know, thoughts and prayers are absolutely useless but direct action and policy change can help. Please, stay on top of your local elections- they are so important. Vote every single time. I know it all feels pretty hopeless right now but we have to keep fighting for a safer future for our kids. 

#fiberart #artist #loominariumfiberart

Focusing on the delicious details. This 10 inch round has handspun yarn, XL rope, 12mm string, hand dyed satin ribbon, velvet, color core rug yarn, tulle, glass beads and vintage lace. Yum.  #wovenwallhanging #roundweaving #handmade

This is a 10” hoop but the rope makes it closer to 14”. A very muted colormelt held up by my (almost) 5 year old. I’m going to have a small shop update this month with small weavings- hopping on my email newsletter is the best way to know when things go up for sale. The sign up box is at the very bottom of my website’s homepage. ✨

#fiberart #fiberartist #roundweaving #comingsoon

I thought I was done making these but then I saw these stand alone wreaths and knew I had to make at least one more forest portal. I added crystals, driftwood and beads to make it extra ✨magical✨

 #cottagecore #mushroomart #goblincore #felted

A tiny frame with big texture. 

I’m going to update my shop sometime next week- there will be 10 small pieces available and my newsletter subscribers will be the first to know when they are listed. 
We have a mushie forest portal, this framed bb, a hanging garden, a muted colormelt and various 10” hoops and lucky horseshoes.
I’ll post a family portrait sometime this weekend so you can see everything that’s coming your way. 
To hop on my email newsletter scroll all the way to the bottom of my website’s homepage ✨

I usually use 14” hoops when I do my fringed pieces but I tried it with a 10” hoop and I really love the look. This piece will be in my drop later this week 👀 
#fiberart #wovenwallhanging #yarnlove #homedecor

Gangs all here! There will be 10 new Loominarium pieces heading to my shop at the end of this week. I had a lot of fun making this little collection of wallhangings and I hope you all love them as much as I do. Don’t forget to hop on my email newsletter to be the first to know the exact time of the drop ✨ 
#wovenwallhanging #prettythings #homedecor #supportlocalartists

A little over a week left to check out Reverie at the @eversonmuseum. I have absolutely loved seeing all the photos you’ve taken so far at the exhibition- it brings me such joy seeing you all there. If you go this weekend please tag me! #atthee  #eversonmuseum #fiberart

Maladaptive Daydreams | My show came down on Monday and I got all my pieces back so I thought I would show you a few of them…this is a 24” hoop that I warped up to intentionally leave open spaces. I went in with layers and layers of fibers to achieve the final look. Black is really hard to photograph but I promise you this piece is so cool in person. 
#fiberart #weaveweird #roundweaving #wovenwallhanging

I finished the woven portion of my sign for @jowonio school’s new sensory room and now I have to go in and do the actual signage portion. I initially drew this frame out to resemble a pond and @toltecworks matched my vision exactly. So far I LOVE IT and can’t wait to finish and see it installed. 
#wovenwallart #handwoven #weaveweird

Post Script | When I said I loved the big rope I wasn’t lying. This one sat half finished for months before I figured out what to do with it— I’m so glad I didn’t give up on this one. It’s a little different than my more typical 24” rounds and absolutely striking on a wall. 

#fiberart #wovenwallhanging #roundweaving #weaveweird

Anyone following May Mayhem over on @cathedral_collective’s page? I CERTAINLY AM. 
I will be hiding this 14” weaving somewhere in the city of Syracuse tomorrow, May 11th. Want to play?? Follow @cathedral_collective and keep your eyes peeled for the clue tomorrow morning on their page. Happy hunting!

My fantastical journey to make a sign for the new sensory room at the beloved @jowonio school. This was one of my favorite projects from this year.

My last #WIP of 2023. This is a 42” hoop and it’s already looking so delicious. Although I slowed down quite a bit this was still a wonderful year for Loominarium. I sent out some beautiful pieces I am super proud of and it still thrills me to know my art lives inside your homes. 
I hope you have a peaceful and cozy closing of the year and I will see you on the other side ❤️🧶
